FIRST EXECUTION:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

>> tool_config_example 

tool_config_example: Argument missing: out_file

usage: tool_config_example [options] out_file input_files...

out_file:       Name of the output file
input_files:    The list of input files

Try --help to get more information.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
The first execution without parameters generates and error message.
The tool reports which was the error (argument "out_file" missing), 
then gives its basic usage to the user and finally suggest to run 
the tool with the option "--help" for a complete information (see below).
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

CORRECT EXECUTION WITHOUT OPTIONS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

>> tool_config_example file.out file001.in file002.in file015.in

Threshold:    126
Output dir:   .
Output file:  file.out
Random Nums:  15 25 
Inputs Files: file001.in file002.in file015.in 
Debug Flag:   off


-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Now the execution was correct and we can see how the tool prints the
correct values. Note that the tool is using its default values.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

CORRECT EXECUTION WITH OPTIONS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

>> tool_config_example -d -r 13 --randoms 99 --out_dir=/mnt/work/data file.out file.in

Threshold:    126
Output dir:   /mnt/work/data
Output file:  file.out
Random Nums:  13 99 
Inputs Files: file.in 
Debug Flag:   on

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Here we can see how to use the command-line options.
Note that in some cases we are using abvreviatures for options 
(-r/--randoms). Also note that flags do not need value (-d).
Finally note that we can use the "=" or not for the long options
(--randoms 99 / --out_dir=/home/me/data)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

SEE THE COMPLETE HELP MESSAGE
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

>> tool_config_example --help

